{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2020-02-03-unav2-integrated-board-prototype/","webpackCompilationHash":"10cd070436fb7f59ed25","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"A*Morale","author":"Alessio Morale"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"53b00c57-e3bd-5fe3-bd3a-a901a38b64e6","excerpt":"During the last few weeks I wanted to take a break from coding and I moved to the ‚Äúdrawing board‚Äù (KiCad üôÇ ) to design a prototype board for the STM32 based‚Ä¶","html":"<p>During the last few weeks I wanted to take a break from coding and I moved to the ‚Äúdrawing board‚Äù (KiCad üôÇ ) to design a prototype board for the STM32 based uNav board. <a href=\"https://github.com/officinerobotiche/unavPCB\">uNav</a> is a motor controller board that integrates with ROS and was was initially based on PIC32. Some time ago I started to rewrite an STM32 version of it, using some generic dev board and it is currently ‚Äúmoving‚Äù my rover <a href=\"https://alessiomorale.com/wordpress/tag/slammer/\">Slammer</a>.</p>\n<p>This is the first iteration of test hardware for uNav2.<br>\nThe board includes a STM32F405 and two DRV8871 drivers. It supports motor current feedback using two INA186 and global battery current/voltage monitor using an INA219. Additionally there is an LM75 temperature monitor ic, a fan output and switching supply for 5V to power the board and the motor encoders.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/gatsby_test/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/071e2/DSC8028.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin: 7vw 0; max-width: 1360px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/gatsby_test/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/53e9f/DSC8028.webp 340w,\n/gatsby_test/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/0991f/DSC8028.webp 680w,\n/gatsby_test/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/9d77c/DSC8028.webp 1360w,\n/gatsby_test/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/24475/DSC8028.webp 2000w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/gatsby_test/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/a0703/DSC8028.jpg 340w,\n/gatsby_test/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/5041d/DSC8028.jpg 680w,\n/gatsby_test/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/fe1b8/DSC8028.jpg 1360w,\n/gatsby_test/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/071e2/DSC8028.jpg 2000w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/gatsby_test/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/fe1b8/DSC8028.jpg\"\n          alt=\"DSC8028\"\n          title=\"\"\n          src=\"/gatsby_test/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/fe1b8/DSC8028.jpg\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n      </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>This is the link to the <a href=\"https://github.com/AlessioMorale/unav2_hardware/tree/master/integrated_board\">repository</a>, there are a few issues (i‚Äôm adding them to the GitHub project to keep track of all changes needed)</p>\n<p>And here is the link to¬†<a href=\"https://htmlpreview.github.io/?https://raw.githubusercontent.com/AlessioMorale/unav2_hardware/master/integrated_board/bom/ibom.html\">Interactive BOM</a>¬†(built with the awesome¬†<a href=\"https://github.com/openscopeproject/InteractiveHtmlBom\">InteractiveHtmlBom plugin</a>)</p>\n<p>The initial tests are ok so far. Hopefully i can post some further update very soon.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"uNav2 Integrated Board prototype","date":"February 03, 2020","description":null,"thumbnail":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/gatsby_test/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/10fb1/DSC8028.jpg","srcSet":"/gatsby_test/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/467b3/DSC8028.jpg 340w,\n/gatsby_test/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/e1ddd/DSC8028.jpg 680w,\n/gatsby_test/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/10fb1/DSC8028.jpg 1360w,\n/gatsby_test/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/883ab/DSC8028.jpg 2000w","sizes":"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/2020-02-03-unav2-integrated-board-prototype/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2019-09-24-nvidia-jetracer/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"NVidia JetRacer","tags":["JetRacer","Jetson nano","Nvidia","ROS"]}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2020-06-11-sensors-and-multifunctional-light-for-slammer/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Sensors and multifunctional light for Slammer","tags":["ROBOT","ROS","slammer","uNav","UNAV2"]}}}}}